1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,600
Ever wondered why one space rock has a tail?

2
00:00:03,600 --> 00:00:09,200
Comets and asteroids are remnants from the solar system's birth, but they’re very different.

3
00:00:09,200 --> 00:00:11,600
Comets are icy, with frozen gases.

4
00:00:11,600 --> 00:00:13,600
When they near the sun?

5
00:00:13,600 --> 00:00:15,600
They develop a glowing tail!

6
00:00:15,600 --> 00:00:19,200
Asteroids, on the other hand, are rocky and metallic.

7
00:00:19,200 --> 00:00:20,800
No ice, no tail.

8
00:00:20,800 --> 00:00:28,000
So, next time you gaze at the sky, remember: one’s a frosty wanderer, the other, a rugged remnant.

9
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:30,000
Curious about more space mysteries?

10
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:31,600
Hit that follow button!
